The paper discusses the performance of deep convolutional networks in object recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture of modern CNNs and their failure to generalize, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses biases in image datasets, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
